      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "c",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A graphics context whose current path is not empty."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "x1",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The x-value, in user space coordinates, for the end point of the first tangent line. The first tangent line is drawn from the current point to (x1,y1)."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "y1",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The y-value, in user space coordinates, for the end point of the first tangent line. The first tangent line is drawn from the current point to (x1,y1)."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "x2",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The x-value, in user space coordinates, for the end point of the second tangent line. The second tangent line is drawn from (x1,y1) to (x2,y2)."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "y2",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The y-value, in user space coordinates, for the end point of the second tangent line. The second tangent line is drawn from (x1,y1) to (x2,y2)."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "radius",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "The radius of the arc, in user space coordinates."
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This method calculates two tangent lines—the first from the current point to the point "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(x1, y1)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", and the second from the point "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(x1, y1)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to the point "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "(x2, y2)"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "—then calculates the start and end points for a circular arc of the specified radius such that the arc is tangent to both lines. Finally, this method approximates that arc with a sequence of cubic Bézier curves and appends those curves to the current path."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If the starting point of the arc (that is, the point where a circle of the specified radius must meet the first tangent line in order to also be tangent to the second line) is not the current point, this method appends a straight line segment from the current point to the starting point of the arc. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The ending point of the arc (that is, the point where a circle of the specified radius must meet the second tangent line in order to also be tangent to the first line) becomes the new current point of the path."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
